title: "Social Security Optimization | Maximize Benefits | Capital Wealth"
description: "Maximize your Social Security benefits with strategic claiming strategies. Expert analysis of spousal benefits, timing, and coordination with retirement income. Lehi, UT."
breadcrumbs:
  - { name: "Home", url: "/" }
  - { name: "Services", url: "/services/" }
  - { name: "Social Security Optimization", url: "/services/social-security/" }
faqSchema:
  - question: "Should I take Social Security at 62?"
    answer: "It depends on your health, other income sources, and tax situation. Claiming at 62 permanently reduces your benefit by up to 30%, but it can make sense if you need the income or have health concerns. We model your specific situation to show you the trade-offs."
  - question: "What are spousal benefits?"
    answer: "A spouse can receive up to 50% of the higher earner's full retirement age benefit. We analyze the optimal claiming sequence for both spouses to maximize your combined lifetime income, including survivor benefit planning."
  - question: "How is Social Security taxed?"
    answer: "Up to 85% of your Social Security benefits can be taxed depending on your other income. The timing of your claim affects your tax bracket and Medicare premiums, which is why we coordinate Social Security planning with your overall tax strategy."
  - question: "When is the best age to claim Social Security?"
    answer: "For most people, delaying until age 70 maximizes lifetime benefits due to the 8% annual increase. However, the right age depends on your health, other income, tax situation, and spousal coordination. We model all scenarios to identify your optimal claiming age."
  - question: "What happens if I work while collecting Social Security?"
    answer: "If you claim before Full Retirement Age and earn above the income limit, your benefits are temporarily reduced. After FRA, you can earn unlimited income with no benefit reduction. We help you navigate the earnings test rules."
---

